            "body": "Alternative discussed in chat: take Lpeg pattern instead of `{glob:string}` object:\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('Whatever', {\r\n  pattern = vim.glob.to_lpeg('**/*.ext'),\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\nOr if we had a `vim.glob.to_vimpat`, we could avoid autocmd-specific changes entirely. But that might be more trouble than it's worth.",
